'''Gabriel Ávalos Stumpfs''' (born 12 October 1990) is a Paraguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|striker]] for [[Argentine Primera División]] club [[Club Atlético Independiente|Independiente]] and the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]].<ref name="SW">{{Soccerway|gabriel-avalos/256435}}</ref>

==Club career==
Born in [[Hohenau, Paraguay|Hohenau]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/avalos-en-su-septimo-club-en-argentina-1779940.html|title=Ávalos, en su séptimo club en Argentina|trans-title=Ávalos, on his seventh club in Argentina|publisher=[[ABC Color]]|language=es|date=22 January 2019|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref> Ávalos began his career with [[Club Atlético Tembetary|Tembetary]] at the age of 17.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ole.com.ar/river-plate/doctor-gol_0_B-uZYgiXf.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190206033457/https://www.ole.com.ar/river-plate/doctor-gol_0_B-uZYgiXf.html|title=Doctor del gol|trans-title=Goal doctor|publisher=[[Olé (sports newspaper)|Olé]]|language=es|date=1 February 2019|archivedate=6 February 2019|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref> After a period with the youth categories of [[Club Libertad|Libertad]], he moved to Argentina with [[Defensores de Cambaceres]] in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tycsports.com/boca-juniors/boca-historia-gabriel-avalos--id369311.html|title=La historia desconocida de Gabriel Ávalos, el goleador por el que negocia Boca|trans-title=The unknown story of Gabriel Ávalos, the goalscorer who Boca negotiate for|publisher=[[TyC Sports]]|language=es|date=14 September 2021|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref>

After playing for the reserve sides of [[Club Atlético Tigre|Tigre]] and [[Gimnasia y Esgrima de La Plata|Gimnasia La Plata]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ole.com.ar/independiente/gabriel-avalos-historia-cambaceres-futbol-argentino-comienzos_0_SaoDvfWFk7.html|title=La primera vez que Gabriel Ávalos se vistió de rojo|trans-title=The first time which Gabriel Ávalos wore red|publisher=[[Olé (sports newspaper)|Olé]]|language=es|date=28 December 2023|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref> Ávalos returned to his home country in 2012 and signed for [[Independiente F.B.C.|Independiente FBC]] in the top tier, but was rarely used. In January 2013, he moved to fellow league team [[Club General Díaz (Luque)|General Díaz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.com.py/edicion-impresa/deportes/avalos-sera-militar-524077.html|title=Ávalos será ‘militar’|trans-title=Ávalos will be a 'military'|publisher=[[ABC Color]]|language=es|date=3 January 2013|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref>

In August 2013, Ávalos signed for [[Deportes Concepción (Chile)|Deportes Concepción]] in the [[Primera B de Chile]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soychile.cl/Concepcion/Deportes/2013/08/13/193232/El-delantero-paraguayo-Gabriel-Avalos-es-el-nuevo-refuerzo-de-Deportes-Concepcion.aspx|title=El delantero paraguayo Gabriel Avalos es el nuevo refuerzo de Deportes Concepción|trans-title=Paraguayan forward Gabriel Avalos is the new addition of Deportes Concepción|publisher=SoyChile.cl|language=es|date=13 August 2013|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref> Roughly one year later, he returned to Argentina with [[Crucero del Norte]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clubcrucerodelnorte.com.ar/novedad.php?id=610|title=Avalos: “Siempre es importante debutar con un gol”|trans-title=Avalos: "It is always important to debut with a goal"|publisher=Crucero del Norte|language=es|date=21 August 2014|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref> being regularly used before suffering a [[knee]] injury in September 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clubcrucerodelnorte.com.ar/novedad.php?id=1453|title=Operaron con éxito a Ávalos|trans-title=Ávalos successfully operated|publisher=Crucero del Norte|language=es|date=11 September 2015|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref>

On 29 June 2016, Ávalos switched teams and countries again after signing a one-year deal with [[Peñarol]] in Uruguay.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/El-paraguayo-Gabriel-Avalos-sera-jugador-de-Penarol-hasta-junio-de-2017-uc312887|title=El paraguayo Gabriel Ávalos será jugador de Peñarol hasta junio de 2017|trans-title=Paraguayan Gabriel Ávalos will be a Peñarol player until June 2017|publisher=Montevideo Portal|language=es|date=29 June 2016|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref> Rarely used, he terminated his link with the club in January 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.padreydecano.com/cms/noticias/el-paraguayo-avalos-rescindio-contrato-con-penarol/|title=El paraguayo Ávalos rescindió contrato con Peñarol|trans-title=Paraguayan Ávalos rescinded his contract with Peñarol|publisher=Padre y Decano|language=es|date=9 January 2017|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref> and spent six months without a club before returning to Argentina with [[Club Atlético Nueva Chicago|Nueva Chicago]], where his career took a turn.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soloascenso.com.ar/notas/quilmes/el-ex-chicago-que-esta-en-el-radar-de-uno-de-los-grandes/166364|title=El ex Chicago que está en el radar de uno de los grandes|trans-title=The former Chicago man who is on the radar of big teams|publisher=Solo Ascenso|language=es|date=1 September 2021|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref>

In July 2018, Ávalos agreed to a deal with [[Godoy Cruz Antonio Tomba|Godoy Cruz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://es.besoccer.com/noticia/gabriel-avalos-nuevo-fichaje-de-godoy-cruz-461604|title=Gabriel Ávalos, nuevo fichaje de Godoy Cruz|trans-title=Gabriel Ávalos, new signing of Godoy Cruz|publisher=BeSoccer|language=es|date=5 July 2018|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref> The following 18 January, he was loaned to [[Club Atlético Patronato|Patronato]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bodegue.net/2019/01/18/avalos-a-patronato/|title=Ávalos a Patronato|trans-title=Ávalos to Patronato|publisher=Lá Página Bodeguera|language=es|date=18 January 2019|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref> where he scored a [[hat-trick]] on his debut against [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] late in that month.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/avalos-el-patron-del-gol-1784085.html|title=Ávalos, el Patrón del gol|trans-title=Ávalos, the Boss of the goal|publisher=[[ABC Color]]|language=es|date=4 February 2019|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref>

On 30 July 2020, Ávalos signed an 18-month contract with [[Argentinos Juniors]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/2020/07/30/gabriel-avalos-en-argentinos-juniors/|title=Gabriel Ávalos, en Argentinos Juniors|trans-title=Gabriel Ávalos, at Argentinos Juniors|publisher=[[ABC Color]]|language=es|date=30 July 2020|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref> On 26 December 2023, after being Argentinos Juniors' top scorer in the [[2023 AFA Liga Profesional de Fútbol|league campaign]] with 12 goals, he moved to [[Club Atlético Independiente|Independiente]] on a three-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://clubaindependiente.com.ar/futbol/noticias/1703597207_avalos-para-el-rojo|title=Ávalos para el Rojo|trans-title=Ávalos for the ''Rojo''|publisher=CA Independiente|language=es|date=26 December 2023|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Ávalos represented the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]] in a 0–0 [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] tie with [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] on 3 June 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/southamerica/matches/match/400104570/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224034612/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/southamerica/matches/match/400104570/|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 24, 2020|title=FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022™ Qualifiers - South America - Matches - Uruguay - Paraguay |website=www.fifa.com}}</ref>

